# Disable subtitles in IINA
# https://codesti.com/issue/iina/iina/4090
# IINA can be configured to use the mpv sub-auto option:
--sub-auto=<no|exact|fuzzy|all>, --no-sub-auto
# Load additional subtitle files matching the video filename. The parameter specifies how external subtitle files are matched. exact is enabled by default.
no:      Don't automatically load external subtitle files.
exact: Load the media filename with subtitle file extension and possibly language suffixes (default).
fuzzy: Load all subs containing the media filename.
all:      Load all subs in the current and --sub-file-paths directories.
# To use this mpv feature follow these instructions:
Start IINA
1.  Click on Preferences… under the IINA menu
2.  The preferences panel appears
3.  On the left side of the panel click on Subtitle
4.  Choose Disabled in the Auto load pull-down button
5.  On the left side of the panel click on Advanced
6.  Slide the Enable advanced settings toggle button to be on (blue)
7.  In the Additional mpv options section click on +
8.  A new entry appears in the table
9.  Double click on name and replace it with sub-auto
10. Double click on value and replace it with fuzzy
11. Make "Use config directory" is UNCHECKED to prevent override. 'echo "sub-auto=no" >> ~/.config/mpv/mpv.conf'  doesn't work in IINA
12. Restart IINA to activate the new settings
